<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-021-830  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 021 830.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 6 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Additional layoffs at McDonnell D computers. (McDonnell DouglasComputer Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   McDonnell Douglas Computer Systems Co. (layoffs).andO;Ticker:    MD.andO;Topic:     Computer industryLayoff.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ADDITIONAL LAYOFFS AT MCDONNELL D COMPUTERS SANTA ANA, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A.,andO;1990 JAN 03 (NB) -- McDonnell Douglas Computer Systems has laid off another100 of its 450 employees as a result of declining sales in the minicomputermarket.andM;In October 1989, McDonnell Douglas laid off 60 people in this division.andP;  Thecurrent layoff affects all departments.andP;  In 1989, McDonnell Douglas hadannounced that the Computer Systems Division was one of the computer- relateddivisions slated for sale or spin-off due to poor performance.andM;The market for minicomputers has been seriously eroded by the move to desktopcomputers and workstations.andP;  Observers have suggested that McDonnell Douglas'sales are also hampered by the company's decision to use the Pick operatingsystem rather than Unix, which has a far larger installed base.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19900105)</TEXT></DOC>